  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nSome of our contract are not abstract from a solidity point of view, but are useless if deployed as is. I'm thinking of contracts like ERC20 that could be deployed with a name an symbol, but the resulting contract would have no way to mint tokens, so the supply would remain 0 forever (making the contract useless).\r\n\r\nIt appears that some users are making that mistake, particularly using Remix:\r\n\r\nRemix will let me deploy ERC20, \r\n\r\n![Capture d‚Äô√©cran du 2023-06-14 11-27-37](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/assets/2432299/385cb8db-742c-4c25-91ee-ae37f2459624)\r\n\r\neven though what I should deploy is MyToken, that inherit ERC20 and adds some minting logic\r\n\r\n![Capture d‚Äô√©cran du 2023-06-14 11-27-48](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/assets/2432299/bd99cca9-bc14-4da5-8e8c-fd1e3659dde5)\r\n\r\nif ERC20 was marked as abstract I would have received a warning when trying to deploy ERC20\r\n\r\n![Capture d‚Äô√©cran du 2023-06-14 11-30-48](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/assets/2432299/29fe834d-02b0-4df1-8f73-6ec37a7d695e)\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nBy default make all our contract \"abstract\". Only remove that keyword for some handpicked contract (VestingWallet, TimelockController, ...)",
